Usage: editTrim [-help] [-keep_floating_stubs]
                [-status {COVER FIXED NOSHIELD ROUTED SHIELD}] [-type {float}] [-all  | -selected  | -nets <net>*] [-all  | -selected  | -layers <string>] [-all  | -selected  | -area {x1 y1 x2 y2}]

-help                   # Prints out the command usage
-all                    # Specifies to trim all special wires and floating
                        # stubs. (bool, optional)
-area {x1 y1 x2 y2}     # Specifies the coordinates for the area from which to
                        # trim the wires. (box, optional)
-keep_floating_stubs    # Specifies whether to keep floating stubs in trim.
                        # (bool, optional)
-layers <string>        # Specifies the layers from which to trim wires.
                        # (string, optional)
-nets <net>*            # Specifies the nets of wires to be trim.
                        # ((net)*, optional)
-selected               # Specifies to trim selected wires. (bool, optional)
-status {COVER FIXED NOSHIELD ROUTED SHIELD}
                        # Specifies the status of wires to trim. (enum, optional)
-type {float}           # Specifies to removes wires that do not have
                        # electrical connections to other wires or pins
                        # (floating wires). (enum, optional)